= <tt>%</tt> (elements) =
<pre>%p thing</pre>

Yields:

<pre><p>thing</p></pre>

= <tt>{}</tt> (attributes) = 

<pre>%meta{'http-equiv' => 'Content-Type', :content => 'text/html; charset=utf-8'}/</pre>

Yields:

<pre><meta http-equiv='Content-Type' content='text/html; charset=utf-8' /></pre>

Note that this example also shows how to produce a self-closing tag; more on this below.

= <tt>/</tt> (comments and self-closing tags) = 

<pre>%br/
/ a comment</pre>

Yields:

<pre><br />
<!-- a comment --></pre>

= <tt>.</tt> (class) = 

<pre>%p.date foo
%p.article.body baz</pre>

Yields:

<pre><p class="date">foo</p>
<p class="article body">baz</p></pre>

= <tt>#</tt> (id) = 

<pre>%p#banner bing</pre>

Yields:

<pre><p id="banner">bing</p></pre>

= Implicit divs = 

If no element is specified with a class (<tt>.</tt>) or id (<tt>#</tt>) then <tt>div</tt> is implicitly assumed:

<pre>#foo bar
.baz bing</pre>

Yields:

<pre><div id="foo">bar</div>
<div class="baz">bing>/div></pre>

= <tt>[]</tt> ("SimplyHelpful" syntax) = 

<pre>%div[@model_object] foo</pre>

Yields:

<pre><div class="class_of_model" id="class_of_model_id">foo</div></pre>

